P(slug="nightlife-guide-goa", date="2026-01-12", cat="City Guide", city="Goa",
  title="The Goa nightlife guide: from beach shacks to sunrise techno",
  excerpt="India's party capital runs on a season, a sound and a set of unwritten rules. Here's how to actually do a Goa night.",
  tags=["Goa","beach","techno","travel"],
  body="""<p>Goa isn't one nightlife scene — it's several stacked on top of each other, and knowing which one you're chasing is the whole game. North Goa is the engine: Anjuna, Vagator, Morjim and Ashwem hold everything from sunset beach shacks to serious after-dark clubs. South Goa is the quiet luxury counter-programme. The season runs roughly November to February, peaking hard around Christmas and New Year.</p>
<h2>The three Goas</h2>
<p><b>Sunset and sundowners.</b> The classic Goa night starts before dark. Cliffside and beachfront spots in Vagator and Anjuna serve the golden-hour crowd with house and downtempo — low-commitment, high-reward, and the best way to ease into an evening.</p>
<p><b>The clubs.</b> After midnight, the crowd migrates to the bigger rooms and open-air floors where touring DJs and India's top selectors play techno and house till late. This is where Goa earns its reputation.</p>
<p><b>Sunrise culture.</b> Goa's real signature is the party that doesn't stop at 2am. The trance lineage runs deep here, and the after-hours, into-the-dawn session is a rite of passage.</p>
<h2>Doing it right</h2>
<ul><li>Rent a scooter — nightlife is spread across kilometres of coast, and cabs get expensive fast.</li><li>Peak season means peak prices and crowds; the shoulder weeks are the local secret.</li><li>Pace yourself. Goa is a marathon scene, not a sprint.</li></ul>
<p>Goa sets the bar for the country. Everything the rest of India's scene does, it does with one eye on the coast.</p>""")

P(slug="nightlife-guide-mumbai", date="2026-01-16", cat="City Guide", city="Mumbai",
  title="Mumbai after dark: rooftops, warehouses and the country's best line-ups",
  excerpt="The city that never sleeps has the deepest club calendar in India. A guide to where the night actually happens.",
  tags=["Mumbai","clubs","rooftop","travel"],
  body="""<p>If Goa is where India parties on holiday, Mumbai is where it parties on a Tuesday. The city has the densest, most consistent nightlife in the country — a real ecosystem of clubs, rooftop bars, warehouse events and gig venues that runs all year, not just in season.</p>
<h2>The lay of the land</h2>
<p><b>Lower Parel &amp; Worli</b> are the glossy heart — high-end clubs, rooftop lounges and the crowd that fills them. <b>Bandra</b> is the cooler, more eclectic west-side scene, heavy on live music, indie gigs and bars with character. <b>Andheri and the northern suburbs</b> host bigger-format events and the warehouse and festival-style shows.</p>
<p>Mumbai is also India's live-music capital. On any given week you can catch touring international acts, homegrown indie bands, hip-hop showcases and full-scale electronic line-ups — often in the same neighbourhood.</p>
<h2>Know before you go</h2>
<ul><li>Weeknights are genuinely good here — the city's size means there's always a crowd out.</li><li>Guest lists and table bookings matter at the marquee venues; walk-ins can be tough on weekends.</li><li>Distances are real. Plan your night around one or two areas rather than criss-crossing the city.</li></ul>
<p>For sheer range and quality of programming, nothing in India touches Mumbai. It's the city every artist wants to play.</p>""")

P(slug="nightlife-guide-delhi", date="2026-01-20", cat="City Guide", city="Delhi NCR",
  title="Delhi NCR nightlife: from Hauz Khas to Gurugram's big rooms",
  excerpt="The capital's scene is loud, ambitious and spread across a giant metro. Here's how to navigate a Delhi-NCR night.",
  tags=["Delhi","Gurugram","clubs","travel"],
  body="""<p>Delhi and its satellite cities form one sprawling nightlife region, and the capital doesn't do anything by halves. Big rooms, big sound, big crowds — NCR's scene is built for scale, and it draws some of the biggest touring names in the country.</p>
<h2>The map</h2>
<p><b>Hauz Khas Village and Aerocity</b> anchor the Delhi-proper going-out crowd — bars, lounges and clubs packed close together. <b>Connaught Place</b> keeps the classic central-Delhi night alive. But much of the serious clubbing has migrated to <b>Gurugram</b>, where the large-format venues host the marquee electronic and Bollywood-commercial nights.</p>
<p>Delhi's crowd loves an occasion — the city responds hard to a well-produced event, a strong headliner, and a night that feels like a statement. Commercial and Bollywood-forward programming does big numbers here alongside the underground.</p>
<h2>Practical notes</h2>
<ul><li>NCR is huge — Gurugram to central Delhi is a serious drive. Pick your zone.</li><li>Winter is peak season; the pleasant months pull everyone out.</li><li>Dress codes at the premium clubs are real and enforced.</li></ul>
<p>For big-stage energy and headline line-ups, Delhi-NCR delivers. It's a scene that likes to go large.</p>""")

P(slug="nightlife-guide-bengaluru", date="2026-01-24", cat="City Guide", city="Bengaluru",
  title="Bengaluru: India's underground and live-music brain",
  excerpt="The country's most discerning music crowd lives here. A guide to Bengaluru's clubs, microbreweries and deep-cut scene.",
  tags=["Bengaluru","underground","live music","travel"],
  body="""<p>Ask DJs and promoters where India's most knowledgeable dancefloor is, and a lot of them will say Bengaluru. The city has a reputation for a crowd that comes for the music itself — patient with a deep set, open to new sounds, and less obsessed with the commercial hits than some of its peers.</p>
<h2>The character</h2>
<p>Bengaluru pioneered India's microbrewery-and-music culture, and it shows: the going-out scene blends craft beer, live gigs and club nights into something uniquely its own. <b>Indiranagar</b> and the central districts are thick with venues, from intimate live rooms to proper electronic floors.</p>
<p>It's also a festival city at heart — home to influential outdoor and sustainability-minded music gatherings that draw crowds who genuinely care about the line-up. The underground house and techno community here is among the healthiest in the country.</p>
<h2>Tips</h2>
<ul><li>The city's deadlines can be earlier than Mumbai or Delhi — start your night sooner.</li><li>Follow the promoters, not just the venues; the best nights are collective-driven.</li><li>Come curious. This crowd rewards adventurous programming.</li></ul>
<p>If you want a dancefloor that listens, Bengaluru is your city.</p>""")

P(slug="nightlife-guide-pune", date="2026-01-28", cat="City Guide", city="Pune",
  title="Pune: the young, loud neighbour that hosts India's biggest festival weekend",
  excerpt="A student city with festival-grade ambitions — and the home of VH1 Supersonic. A guide to Pune's nightlife.",
  tags=["Pune","festival","students","travel"],
  body="""<p>Pune punches above its weight. A massive student and young-professional population keeps the city's nightlife energetic and affordable, and once a year Pune becomes the centre of India's festival calendar when VH1 Supersonic rolls into town.</p>
<h2>The scene</h2>
<p><b>Koregaon Park</b> is the traditional going-out heart — clubs, lounges and bars clustered together. The wider city has embraced the microbrewery-and-music model, and the crowd skews young, up-for-it, and price-conscious in the best way.</p>
<p>The Supersonic weekend transforms everything. For a few days each year, the festival pulls international and Indian headliners across techno, house, bass and pop, and the whole city's nightlife orbits around it — pre-parties, after-parties, and a citywide surge in energy.</p>
<h2>Good to know</h2>
<ul><li>Festival weekend books out fast — accommodation and events fill weeks ahead.</li><li>The student energy means weeknights stay lively through term time.</li><li>Pune pairs well with a Mumbai trip — they're a short hop apart.</li></ul>
<p>For festival culture and youthful energy, Pune is one of India's essential stops.</p>""")

P(slug="nightlife-guide-hyderabad", date="2026-02-01", cat="City Guide", city="Hyderabad",
  title="Hyderabad nightlife: high-rise clubs and a fast-rising scene",
  excerpt="The city's tech boom brought a nightlife boom with it. A guide to Hyderabad's clubs, rooftops and events.",
  tags=["Hyderabad","clubs","rooftop","travel"],
  body="""<p>Hyderabad's nightlife has grown up fast alongside its tech economy. Once a quieter going-out city, it now has a confident scene of high-rise clubs, rooftop lounges and a growing calendar of electronic and commercial events pulling touring names.</p>
<h2>Where it happens</h2>
<p><b>Jubilee Hills and Banjara Hills</b> hold the premium clubs and lounges, while the <b>HITEC City / Gachibowli</b> corridor serves the young tech crowd with newer, high-energy venues. The city leans commercial and Bollywood-forward on the mainstream nights, with a small but committed underground community pushing house and techno.</p>
<p>Hyderabad's crowd loves a big production, and promoters increasingly bring festival-grade shows to the city. It's a scene on a clear upward curve.</p>
<h2>Tips</h2>
<ul><li>The premium clubs run strict dress codes and reservations.</li><li>Weekend programming is where the marquee events land.</li><li>Pleasant winter months are peak going-out season.</li></ul>
<p>Rising, ambitious, and increasingly on the touring circuit — Hyderabad is worth watching.</p>""")

P(slug="nightlife-guide-udaipur", date="2026-02-05", cat="City Guide", city="Udaipur",
  title="Udaipur nightlife: lakeside parties in the city of lakes",
  excerpt="Palaces, lakes and — increasingly — a proper party scene. Your guide to going out in Udaipur, Pronite's home turf.",
  tags=["Udaipur","lakeside","pool party","travel"],
  body="""<p>Udaipur built its fame on palaces and lakes, but there's a reason a nightlife collective grew up here. The same setting that makes the city a wedding and honeymoon capital makes it extraordinary for events — rooftop bars with palace views, lakeside resorts, and open-air venues that no metro can replicate.</p>
<h2>The Udaipur difference</h2>
<p>This isn't a warehouse-and-basement scene. Udaipur's edge is the backdrop: pool parties by the water, camping nights under clear Rajasthan skies, and sundowners with a view most cities would charge a fortune for. It's boutique by nature — curated events over a dense club circuit.</p>
<p>Pronite has spent years building the city's party calendar around that advantage — Holi pool parties, open-air techno, Bollywood nights and New Year's countdowns at The Udaisarovar and the city's best venues. The scene is small but genuinely special.</p>
<h2>Planning a night</h2>
<ul><li>Events here are seasonal and often ticketed or guest-list only — plan ahead.</li><li>Winter and the festival stretch (Holi, NYE) are peak.</li><li>Pair the party with a stay — Udaipur rewards a full weekend.</li></ul>
<p>For a party with a view you'll actually remember, few Indian cities compete with Udaipur.</p>""")

P(slug="nightlife-guide-jaipur", date="2026-02-09", cat="City Guide", city="Jaipur",
  title="Jaipur nightlife: the Pink City's rooftops and heritage venues",
  excerpt="Rajasthan's capital blends heritage glamour with a growing club and event scene. Here's the lay of the land.",
  tags=["Jaipur","Rajasthan","rooftop","travel"],
  body="""<p>Jaipur's nightlife trades on the same asset as the rest of Rajasthan: atmosphere. Heritage hotels, rooftop bars overlooking the old city, and palace-grade event venues give the Pink City a going-out scene that leans glamorous and occasion-driven.</p>
<h2>The scene</h2>
<p>The city's premium hotels and rooftop lounges anchor the upscale night, while a handful of clubs serve the commercial and Bollywood crowd. Jaipur really comes alive around <b>weddings and the festival season</b> — the city's event infrastructure is world-class, and that spills over into nightlife whenever there's an occasion.</p>
<p>Like Udaipur, Jaipur is boutique rather than dense — the magic is in the settings, not the sheer number of venues. Holi and New Year draw the biggest crowds and the best-produced events.</p>
<h2>Tips</h2>
<ul><li>Heritage venues often mean dress codes and advance booking.</li><li>Festival-season events are the highlight — plan around Holi and NYE.</li><li>The old-city rooftops are unbeatable for a sundowner.</li></ul>
<p>For heritage glamour with a beat, Jaipur delivers a distinctly Rajasthani night out.</p>""")

P(slug="nightlife-guide-chandigarh", date="2026-02-13", cat="City Guide", city="Chandigarh",
  title="Chandigarh nightlife: the North's polished party city",
  excerpt="Clean, planned and surprisingly lively — Chandigarh's Sector clubs and Punjabi energy make for a big night out.",
  tags=["Chandigarh","Punjab","clubs","travel"],
  body="""<p>Chandigarh brings a very particular energy to a night out — polished, high-spending, and soundtracked by the Punjabi-pop juggernaut that dominates North Indian dancefloors. The city's planned Sectors hold a compact, lively cluster of clubs and lounges that go hard on the weekend.</p>
<h2>The character</h2>
<p>Sectors 26 and 7, along with the neighbouring hubs, form the going-out core. The sound here is unapologetically commercial — Punjabi hits, Bollywood, and chart bangers that the crowd knows every word of. It's a scene built for celebration, not for underground exploration.</p>
<p>Chandigarh also feeds the wider Punjab circuit — the region's love of big, loud, dressed-up nights makes it one of the most reliably energetic crowds in the country.</p>
<h2>Tips</h2>
<ul><li>Weekends are the main event; weeknights are quieter.</li><li>Come dressed to impress — the crowd does.</li><li>Expect Punjabi and Bollywood to dominate the floor.</li></ul>
<p>For a high-energy, sing-every-word kind of night, Chandigarh is North India at its most fun.</p>""")

P(slug="nightlife-guide-kolkata", date="2026-02-17", cat="City Guide", city="Kolkata",
  title="Kolkata nightlife: live music, culture and Park Street after dark",
  excerpt="The City of Joy parties with soul. A guide to Kolkata's legendary live scene and its clubs.",
  tags=["Kolkata","live music","Park Street","travel"],
  body="""<p>Kolkata does nightlife with a cultural streak no other Indian city quite matches. This is a place with a genuine live-music soul — jazz, rock, blues and Bengali bands are woven into the going-out fabric, and the historic <b>Park Street</b> strip has been the beating heart of it for generations.</p>
<h2>The scene</h2>
<p>Park Street's restaurants, bars and live-music institutions anchor the classic Kolkata night. Beyond it, the city has modern clubs and lounges serving the commercial and electronic crowd, but the live circuit is what gives Kolkata its identity — few cities take a band on stage as seriously.</p>
<p>The crowd here is warm, unpretentious and up for a long evening. Festivals and the year-end season bring a surge of events, and the city's love of a good time is genuinely infectious.</p>
<h2>Tips</h2>
<ul><li>Seek out the live venues — they're the city's real speciality.</li><li>The Christmas-to-New-Year stretch on Park Street is legendary.</li><li>Kolkata rewards a slower, conversational night as much as a dancefloor one.</li></ul>
<p>For soul, history and live music, Kolkata is one of a kind.</p>""")

P(slug="nightlife-guide-chennai", date="2026-02-21", cat="City Guide", city="Chennai",
  title="Chennai nightlife: a quieter coast with a committed crowd",
  excerpt="Chennai plays it cooler than the party metros, but its clubs, gigs and beach energy reward those who look.",
  tags=["Chennai","clubs","coast","travel"],
  body="""<p>Chennai's nightlife is more understated than Mumbai's or Delhi's, shaped by earlier deadlines and a more low-key going-out culture — but the crowd that does come out is loyal, and the scene has grown steadily. What it lacks in volume it makes up in a distinct South Indian flavour.</p>
<h2>Where to look</h2>
<p>The premium hotels and standalone clubs in the central and coastal districts hold the mainstream night, with commercial and Bollywood-Tamil programming leading the floor. A small electronic and live-music community keeps things interesting for those who dig deeper, and the city's proximity to the coast lends a relaxed, beach-adjacent energy.</p>
<p>Chennai is a city where the pre-dinner and dinner-drinks culture is strong, and the night often centres on great food and good company as much as a dancefloor.</p>
<h2>Tips</h2>
<ul><li>Start early — the city winds down sooner than the northern metros.</li><li>Hotel venues are your safest bet for a reliable night.</li><li>Look for the live gigs and one-off electronic events.</li></ul>
<p>Lower-key but genuine, Chennai rewards the curious.</p>""")

